# Replenish Order Line

This is a request, within a specific Replenish Order, for a specified number of copies of some 
specified Print Medium. Some people would refer to this class as "Replenish Order Details."

◇

attributes:
    quantity:
        name: "quantity"
        details: The number of quantities of the selected Print Medium being requested.
        rules: 1 .. unconstrained to the nearest whole number

states:

  Open:
    details: The line is created and can be added to.

events:

    "«new»":
        details: Create this Replenish Order Line.
        parameters:
            - name: replenish order
              source: somewhere
            - name: print medium
              source: somewhere
            - name: qty
              source: somewhere

    Add:
        details: Add more quantity to the order line.
        parameters:
            - name: qty
              source: somewhere

    Received:
        details: The Publisher has received this order line.

actions:

    Initialize:
        details: Start a new Replenish Order.
        requires:
            - qty is consistent with range of .quantity
        guarantees:
            - |
                one new Replenish Order Line exists with:
                    -quantity == qty
                    this line linked to Replenish Order and Print Medium

    AddQuantity:
        details: Increase the quantity of an existing order line.
        requires:
            - qty > 0
        guarantees:
            - post(.quanity) == pre(quantity) + qty
 
    MarkAsReceived:
        details: This Print Medium has been added to the stocks. 
        guarantees:
            - restock(.quantity) has been signaled for the linked Print Medium. 

transitions:

    - {from: "", event: "«new»", to: "Open", action: "Initialize"}

    - {from: "Open", event: "Add", to: "Open", action: "AddQuantity"}
    - {from: "Open", event: "Received", to: "", action: "MarkAsReceived"}

